approachcustom.heading: My view of psychological health
approachcustom.content: Psychological health is an essential building block to a sound, integrated and wholesome human being. As human beings all of us have a path that we walk on and some it's more arduous than others. Having the ability to work with difficulties without falling apart or without it affecting our functioning is only one part of the psychological health or well being. The other part of the psychological wellbeing is the ability to transform or in today's terms upgrade the existing inner being. We can all become better version of ourselves by looking at the world around us and within us. The world around us is in constant dialogue with our inner world of emotions, thoughts and motivations. Balancing the two is like infusing life in the psychological wellbeing. The world can consume you, overwhelm you or can also be doorways to your betterment. Developing this capacity to reflect can help you to create your own ecosystem of support for maintaining your inner balance and compassion. Compassion, ability to bring joy, be creative, fold hands in gratitude are also components of psychological health. So is healthy anger (to strive for betterment of human conditions), sadness and fear. Therapy helps you bring in the balance in your thinking, feeling and intending to create the psychological wellbeing.
